<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing a skid plate system is an essential modification for any serious off-roader, particularly for those who take their Jeep into rugged terrain. In this tutorial, we’ll be diving into the installation of the Rock Hard 4X4 skid plate system targeting the motor, transmission, and transfer case of the 2015 Jeep Wrangler JKU. This setup not only enhances protection but also provides peace of mind when tackling challenging trails.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>We will be addressing the step-by-step process for installing the skid plates, discussing the necessary tools and components, and highlighting key considerations to ensure a successful installation. By the end of this article, you will have a comprehensive understanding of how to strengthen your Jeep’s underbody.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><p>Here’s a simplified version of the installation procedure:</p><ol><li><strong>Gather Your Tools:</strong> You'll need a set of wrenches, sockets (particularly 3/4 inch or 19mm), a hammer, and hardwearing bolts that typically come with the kit.</li><li><strong>Preparation:</strong> Ensure your vehicle is safely lifted and secured. It’s important to have adequate working space underneath to maneuver.</li><li><strong>Install the Transfer Case Skid Plate:</strong> Position the transfer case skid into place first, securing it with the rear bolts. This helps align everything correctly since the motor transmission skid will overlap it.</li><li><strong>Attach the Motor Mount Brackets:</strong> Use the specific brackets provided in the kit (the driver side has a bend in the middle, while the passenger side does not) and attach them to the motor mount. Make sure they are correctly aligned for a snug fit.</li><li><strong>Test Fit and Adjust:</strong> Before tightening everything down, test fit all parts to ensure that there is no obstruction with other components such as the exhaust. You may rotate components slightly if space is tight.</li><li><strong>Tighten Your Bolts:</strong> Once you have verified everything aligns correctly, proceed to tighten all bolts securely. Double-check each connection for tightness to avoid loose parts on the trail.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><p>Here are a few additional tips to keep in mind during your installation:</p><ul><li><strong>Check Exhaust Clearance:</strong> Ensure your exhaust doesn’t contact the skid plate, especially if you are using spacers. A rattling exhaust can lead to bigger issues down the line.</li><li><strong>Utilize the Right Brackets:</strong> The brackets can be installed on either side, but for most users, keeping them inside will maintain a cleaner look while giving enough clearance for suspension articulation.</li><li><strong>Take Your Time:</strong> Don’t rush through the installation. Take the time to ensure everything fits properly; it's much easier than fixing a problem later.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Installing a skid plate system such as the Rock Hard 4X4 is a formidable step towards enhancing the durability and off-road capability of your Jeep Wrangler JKU. Not only does it provide keen protection against rocks and debris but it also assists in preserving the integrity of your vehicle’s components. With a straightforward installation process and relatively minimal tools required, dedicated Jeep owners can accomplish this task with confidence. Happy wheeling!</p>

